cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and summarization. The use of a discriminative model and learned weights for features suggests it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on improving coherence and cross-sentence relationships suggests it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of compression rules and dependencies suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
